        "answer_count": 1,
        "title": "Setting a heap memory above 4096MB on Karaf",
        "body": "<p>I'm using a java application which requires a lot of memory, and I'd like to be able to set the maximum available memory for the JVM to a value above 4096MB, such as 8192MB.<\/p>\n\n<p>I tried using the following parameter: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>wrapper.java.maxmemory\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>which seems to work fine under the 4096MB threshold, but not above (it is stuck at something like 3.7GB or so).<\/p>\n\n<p>I'm using a 64b JVM.<\/p>\n\n<p>Where is the piece of code that prevents me from going above 4096MB?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 35368821,
